name: body mass

name: antenna
definition: Paired appendages used for sensing in arthropods

name: apposition eye
definition: A compound eye with no separation between the crystalline-cone layer and the retinula, each rhabdom receiving light only from its own corneal lens.

name: carapace
definition: A bony or chitinous case or shield covering the back or part of the back of an animal (as a turtle or crab).

name: cercus
definition: Paired appendages on the rear-most segments of many arthropods
resource: Ontology for the Anatomy of the Insect SkeletoMuscular system (AISM)

name: compound eye
definition: A light sensing organ composed of multiple ommatidia, visual units consisting of a limited number of rhabdomeric photoreceptor cells, cornea-secreting epithelial cells, interommatidial pigment cells, and sometimes crystalline cone cells

name: elytron
definition: A modified, hardened forewing of certain insect orders

name: eye
definition: Visual organ

name: eyestalk
definition: A protrusion that extends an eye away from the body

name: gill
definition: A respiratory organ found in many aquatic organisms that extracts dissolved oxygen from water

name: gonopod
definition: Specialized appendages of various arthropods used in reproduction or egg-laying

name: haltere
definition: A pair of small club-shaped organs on the body of some flying insects

name: hemelytron
definition: An insect's forewing with both membranous and hardened portions

name: horn
definition: Pointed projection on the head of various animals

name: leg
definition: A leg is a weight-bearing and locomotive anatomical structure, usually having a columnar shape.

name: ocellus
definition: small simple eyes, found in many invertebrates, usually consisting of a few sensory cells and a single lens

name: ovipositor
definition: A tube-like organ used by some animals, especially insects, for the laying of eggs

name: proboscis
definition: A tubular feeding and sucking organ

name: pterostigma
definition: A group of specialized cells in the outer wings of insects

name: superposition eye
definition: refracting, reflecting and parabolic superposition eyes

name: tympanal organ
definition: hearing organ in insects, consisting of a membrane (tympanum) stretched across a frame backed by an air sac and associated sensory neurons

name: wing
definition: Complete wing

name: apterous
definition: Wings are absent

name: auditory system
definition: is the sensory system for the sense of hearing

name: bioluminescent
definition: Has this organism been observed to produce and transmit light?

name: blind
definition: complete or nearly complete lack of vision

name: brachypterous
synonyms: nonfunctional wings, reduced wings, microptery, micropterous
definition: The presence of short wings, not functional as organs of flight

name: has wings
definition: Wings are present

name: secondarily apterous
definition: The absence of wings in organisms that are descended from winged ancestors

name: aristate antenna
definition: Having a slender, sharp, or spiny tip.

name: lamellate antenna
definition: This term is used especially to describe certain insect antennae in which the last segments are so shaped into a compact club of flat plates

name: serrate antenna
definition: Having tooth-like projections on one side, as in a saw

name: flabellate antenna
definition: Fan-shaped; having parts or segments that are flattened and lengthened on one side, such that they are long and narrow

name: moniliform antenna
definition: Having a form resembling a string of beads, where the component parts or segments are more or less uniform in size and are spherical or rounded in shape

name: setaceous antenna
definition: Of, relating to, or resembling a seta or bristle; bristly

name: geniculate antenna
definition: Having kneelike joints; able to bend at an abrupt angle

name: plumose antenna
synonyms: plumose antennae, feathery antennae, plumelike antennae
definition: Having hairs, or other parts, arranged along an axis like a feather

name: pectinate antenna
definition: Having segments which are greatly lengthened to one side

name: clavate antenna
synonyms: clavate antennae, claviform antennae, clubbed antennae
definition: Resembling a club, becoming increasingly wide from the base to the distal end

name: stylate antenna
definition: A small, thin, pointed body part
